HEADWORD: Syringin
<hw>Sy*rin"gin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A glucoside found in the bark of the lilac (<gen>Syringa</gen>) and
extracted as a white crystalline substance; -- formerly called also
<altname>lilacin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

